<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/879> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #879" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "With the Dictator Poetelius, according to Fast. Cap.; Degrassi 36f., 101, 418f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/871> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #871" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Livy does not state who commanded the Roman force that recovered Luceria (9.26). Diod. (19.72.8-9) dates the colony in the previous year." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/870> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #870" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 9.24.1; Diod. 19.73.1; Fast. Cap. (names entire); Chr. 354 (Libone et Longo III); Fast. Hyd. (Saminte et Longo); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; Degrassi 36f., 110, 418f. The Consuls captured Sora and the Ausonian towns,\n     and defeated a Samnite force in Campania (Liv. 9.24-25, and 27; cf. Diod. 19.76.1-5). Sulpicius celebrated a triumph (Act. Tr., Degrassi 70f., 542; not mentioned by Livy). On Poetelius, cf. Lübker no. 3." .
